  - meta-learning
  - scientific method
  - first principles
  - ai safety
abstract: >-
  What if the AI agent guessed first? 251 experiments across three agent
  conditions — blind search, LLM reflection, and LLM prediction-error —
  show that the predicting agent adapted to a 5x compute shift on its
  first try. The reflecting agent took 7 tries. The searching agent never
  caught up. Prediction error is the source of transfer in autonomous research.
